How I ſucceeded in Dublin, as an Actor you may have heard, and a Gentleman, a Well-wiſher of mine, having publiſhed an Account of the Iriſh Theatre in a Letter from Dublin to a Friend in London, printed in the Inſpector, or London Daily Advertiſer, laſt Summer, which I ſend you incloſed; 
                  See the Appendix, p. 18. to that I refer you, as far as relates to Stage Affairs:—As to my Conduct off the Stage: I may affirm I lived reputably, and decently; and my Mind being more at Eaſe while I was there for three Years, than it had been for a long time before, I know of No Irregularities I gave way


to there, that could either bring Shame to myſelf, or cauſe my Friends to bluſh for me.
